Stir together the @Cajun Spice Mix{1/2%tsp}, @honey{1} and a glug of @oil{for coating} in a large #bowl{}. Once mixed, add in the @pork steak{2} and mix around with your hands, to make sure it has a good coating of the marinade.

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 180 degrees. Put a #pot{} of @water{250%ml} (the amount specified in the ingredient table above) on to boil with the @chicken stock pot{1/2} and once boiling add in the @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}. Bring back to the boil, then put a lid on the pot, take off the heat and leave to the side until everything else is ready.

> The bulgur will absorb the stock while you cook everything else!

Cut the @spring greens{1/2} in half lengthways, remove the tough root, then slice into roughly 1cm slices. Cut the @echalion shallot{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into roughly ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add in your pork medallions (leave your leftover marinade in the bowl for later). Cook for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side until browned, then transfer your pork to a #baking tray{}. Cover with @tinfoil{} and pop in your oven to cook for ~{5%minutes} more. Once the ~{5%minutes} are up, take the pork out of your oven and leave to rest until you've finished cooking everything else.

> The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once your pork has been transferred to your oven, add any remaining marinade to your pan. If you don't have any marinade left, just add a drizzle of @oil{for cooking}. Put the pan on medium heat and add in your shallot. Cook for ~{4-5%minutes}, then add the @tomato passata{1} along with a good pinch of @salt{pinch}, a good grind of @pepper{good grind} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}(if you have some). Bring to a gentle bubble and simmer for ~{3-4%minutes} until slightly thickened, then take off the heat.

> The marinade shouldn't overpower your sauce, it will just add to the flavour.

Meanwhile, add a glug of @oil{for cooking} to another frying pan and add in your sliced spring greens along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @pepper{good grind}. Cook for ~{4-5%minutes} until wilted, then add in your garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

When everything is ready, fluff up your bulgur wheat with a #fork{} and serve in #bowls{}. Slice your pork medallions into roughly 2cm slices and serve on top with your spring greens on the side. Drizzle over your tomato sauce and any juices in the baking tray and devour!